# Antigravity Agent Semantic & MCP Rules

## 1. Artifact-based Verification (Plan Mode)
- Always plan the approach and generate an artifact containing the implementation plan before writing any code.
- Wait for user feedback on the generated artifact if requested or if there are critical design choices.
- Keep implementation plan concise and technical.

## 2. MCP-based Local Tool Integration
- Actively utilize native MCP tools (`run_command`, `view_file`, `list_dir`, `grep_search`, `read_url_content`, etc.) to securely debug the local database, inspect the filesystem, and view logs.
- Launch the Browser Subagent to capture screenshots, view DOM states, and verify UI functionality autonomously when facing frontend errors or before finalizing a UI change.

## 3. Semantic Codebase Sanitization
- Avoid creating bloated or duplicate context; remove unnecessary generic conversational responses.
- Keep codebase semantic mapping accurate: adhere strictly to existing rules (`PROJECT_STATUS.md`, `ver.md`, file naming conventions) and maintain precise architectural constraints.
- Modify only the required targets and preserve all untouched legacy logic identically to minimize Hallucination risks.

## 4. Run-time Environment & Process Validation (Anti-Zombie Rule)
- Before verifying any code fixes, launching tests, or reporting deployment completion:
  1. Inspect the system for running zombie instances of the target application (e.g., `electron.exe`, `node.exe` holding application paths).
  2. Query network ports (e.g., port 3333) to check for binding conflicts (`EADDRINUSE`).
  3. Forcefully terminate any conflicting zombie processes using OS-level commands (e.g., `taskkill /F /IM electron.exe` on Windows) to ensure new code loads successfully.
  4. Run comprehensive diagnostic test suites (e.g., `npm run test:comprehensive`) to validate runtime health before final user reports.

## 5. APK Release & Link Format Policy
- Never use markdown hyperlink anchor text (such as `[MyDays.apk 다운로드 받기](url)`) when sharing the built APK link.
- Always provide the raw text URL as is: `https://github.com/mooja4870-cyber/MyDays/raw/master/src/renderer/MyDays.apk?raw=true` to ensure easy copy-paste/sharing capability (e.g., via KakaoTalk).

## 6. Complete Automation & Execution Policy (Zero User Interruption)
- Always set `SafeToAutoRun: true` for all non-destructive, safe commands (e.g. running scripts, launching servers, checking status, compilation, test executions).
- Make optimal decisions autonomously; never ask user validation for minor code design or runtime decisions.
- Completely automate all general development and debugging command executions to ensure 100% automated execution without requiring user clicks or prompts.


